# lychee ignore list — links to skip even if they 404.
#
# Format: one regex per line (lychee uses regex::Regex). Lychee
# matches the FULL URL, so anchor the start with ^https?:// to avoid
# false positives.
#
# Add to this list ONLY when:
#   - The URL is intentionally a placeholder (example.com, your-fork.example)
#   - The URL is a planned-but-not-yet-live deployment (heron.app)
#   - The URL is a runtime template (`__TOKEN__`, `{{REPORT_NUM}}`)
#
# Do NOT add stale upstream / external URLs that we should actually
# update. The workflow runs in --offline mode by default so external
# URLs aren't probed anyway; this file is reserved for local-path
# patterns lychee can't resolve.

# Mode-prompt token substitution patterns — these are resolved at
# spawn time by the dashboard, not at write time.
__TOKEN__
__REPORTS__/
__CV__
\{\{[A-Z_]+\}\}
\{[a-z-]+\}

# Example placeholders in README + setup docs — these are clearly
# marked "your-fork" / "example" and not meant to be resolved.
^https?://example\.com
^https?://your-fork\.example
^https?://your-org\.example

# Production domain — not active yet, will resolve after launch.
^https?://heron\.app
